                            <comment id="486089" author="simmonsja" created="Sat, 31 Jan 2026 01:34:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I tested this locally and it passed. Are you still seeing failures?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I do see&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;obd_mount.c:230:lustre_add_mgc_failnodes()) MGC2601:8c1:c100:4ac0::32f4@tcp: can&apos;t add failover NID 2601:8c1:c100:4ac0:71a3:6be1:61c2:8dd2@tcp, rc = -75&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;lustre_add_mgc_failnodes() breaks by copying NID into an obd_uuid so it gets truncated and then calls indirectly client_import_add_conn(). We really should be calling client_import_add_nids_to_conn().&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="485230" author="yujian" created="Sat, 24 Jan 2026 08:11:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 on master: &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/4e4a5d72-a76a-43a9-8391-72b03b79e333&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/4e4a5d72-a76a-43a9-8391-72b03b79e333&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
